Saw both of them perched about 15 minutes later on different parts of the prison rooftops.  Perhaps one had a meal they were fighting over.  Or, maybe it was a territorial dispute.

TRIP COMMENTS: Property Big Sit year 4.  Total species count was 52.  Last year's count was 48 species.  Fairly productive but I was hoping for more given the favorable NW winds and the Birdcast migration indicating there would be a good nocturnal movement.  NFC results were underwhelming.  This was the coldest Big Sit I can remember, even in the afternoon I was only comfortable when I moved into the sun.  I had a nice variety of raptors but really struck out on warblers.----Seven new birds were added to the Big Sit bringing the cumulative total up to 75.  Also added one new mammal to the count.----New birds added to the count: Red-shouldered hawk, Peregrine falcon, Tree swallow, House wren, Gray catbird, Dark-eyed junco, Common yellowthroat----Weather: Partly cloudy to start but quickly clearing. 48F rising to 55F.  Winds NW at 3-10 mph. One shooting star.----Butterflies: Cabbage white 2, Monarch (2 - high and headed south)----Mammals: Eastern cottontail (new for the Big Sit), Eastern gray squirrel 2
